This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve the performance of a neural network model for answering crossword questions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bidirectional LSTM, which is a type of neural network used in natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of sub-word unit segmentation, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
